@NODE "rexx" "ARexx Commands"

Each Rename GUI has an MUI arexx port

the name of the first open is SCALOS_RENAME.1 then SCALOS_RENAME.2 and so on.

they have all the tradidional functions of any mui application plus 2 extra commands.

If you open a rename window and type the following text in a shell...

@{b}Rx "address value SCALOS_RENAME.1 ; 'help ram:rename.help'@{ub}

Then Ram:Rename.help will contain the following...

-------------snip---------------------

Standard-Commands:

Command      Template
-------      --------
quit         FORCE/S
hide
deactivate
show
activate
info         ITEM/A
help         FILE/A


Commands for application "Scalos Rename":

Command      Template
-------      --------
SETPREFS
ADDFILE      PATH/A

-------------snip---------------------

See the MUI guide for the Standard-Commands (ALL MUI apps have those)

Commands i have added are thus...

@{b}SETPREFS@{ub}

Example:
/* */
address value SCALOS_RENAME.1
'SETPREFS'

Function:
Re-reads the Prefs file and updates the changes.

Note:
Using Save/Use/Refresh in the prefs searches for all open
arexx rename ports and uses the SETPREFS command on them.


---------------
@{b}ADDFILE      PATH/A@{ub}

Example:
/* */
file='ram:file_to_rename'
address value SCALOS_RENAME.1
'ADDFILE "'file'"'

Function:
Adds a new file to the list.
@ENDNODE

